    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-12T17:20:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-11T15:00:00-05:00" n="612"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d612">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.8221/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Walton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName> [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1937-12-12T17:20:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1937-12-11T15:00:00-05:00">undated</date>].<lb/>[Received
                        December 12, 1937—5:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. Your 37, December 11, 3 p.m.<note n="26" xml:id="d612fn26">Not
                        printed.</note> Liberian Government has accepted all counter proposals
                    relative to consular convention. Expect to secure similar action with respect to
                    commercial treaty.<note n="27" xml:id="d612fn27">See <ref target="#pg_785">pp.
                            785</ref> ff.</note> I have never had any intention of concluding and
                    signing treaties unless I strictly adhered to the Department’s instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
